    "breadcrumb": "Competency-Based Assessment \u003e Competencies",
    "content": "Analyze Computational Systems I can explain the behavior of computational systems by investigating their components, interactions, and execution.\nI analyze software and computing systems to determine how they operate, identify sources of behavior, and predict outcomes under varying conditions.\nDevelop Abstractions I can create and apply abstractions that reduce complexity while preserving essential characteristics of a problem or system.\nI organize information, processes, and system components into meaningful models that support understanding, communication, and solution development.\nApply Formal Reasoning I can use logical, mathematical, and formal methods to analyze computational problems and justify conclusions.\nI construct and evaluate arguments, proofs, and formal representations to reason about the correctness and behavior of computational systems.\nEvaluate Algorithmic Solutions I can evaluate alternative algorithms and representations by analyzing their correctness, performance, and tradeoffs.\nI select and justify computational approaches using theoretical and empirical evidence appropriate to the problem context.",
